{"title_page": "Federico Rampini", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian journalist and writer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Federico Rampini\n| image         = Federico Rampini - Festival Economia 2015.JPG\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1956|03|25}}\n| birth_place   = Genoa, Italy\n| nationality   = Italian, American\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Journalist, writer, lecturer\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Federico Rampini''' (born 25 March 1956) is an Italian [[journalist]], [[writer]], and [[lecturer]] who holds both Italian and American citizenship.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/trump-trashes-us-allies-china-seizes-future/|title=While Trump Trashes US Allies, China Seizes the Future|last=Rampini|first=Federico|date=12 June 2018|journal=[[The Nation]]|location=U.S.|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iicchicago.esteri.it/iic_chicago/it/gli_eventi/calendario/book-presentation-when-our-history.html|title=Book Presentation: \"When Our History Begins\" by Federico Rampini, Chief New York Correspondent for Italy's La Repubblica Newspaper|website=iicchicago.esteri.it|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Italy)]]|location=Italy|language=it-it|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>  He served as deputy editor of ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'', and has worked as chief  foreign correspondent for ''[[La Repubblica]]'' since 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ces.fas.harvard.edu/people/federico-rampini|title=Federico Rampini|last=University|first=Harvard|date=20 November 2019|website=Center for European Studies at Harvard University|publisher=[[Harvard University]]|location=Massachusetts, U.S.|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref> He has been residing in the United States since 2000.<ref name=\"Federico Rampini\">{{cite web|url=http://www.premiohemingway.it|title=Federico Rampini|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> He is the 2019 receipient of the [[Premio Hemingway|Ernest Hemmingway Prize]].<ref name=\"hemingwayaward\">{{cite web |title=Federico Rampini Premio Hemingway 2019 per la sezione \"Testimone del nostro tempo\" {{!}} 35^ Edizione del Premio Hemingway 19 / 23 GIUGNO 2019 - LIGNANO |url=http://www.premiohemingway.it/all-event-list/federico-rampini-premio-hemingway-2019-per-la-sezione-testimone-del-nostro-tempo/ |website=www.premiohemingway.it |accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life, education and family==\nRampini was born in [[Genoa]], Italy on March 25, 1956, and was raised in [[Brussels]] due to his father's work at the [[European Commission]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\">{{cite interview |last=Rampini |first=Federico |interviewer=[[Harry Kreisler]] |title=Federico Rampini Interview {{!}} Background |type=Transcript of video |url=http://globetrotter.berkeley.edu/people2/Rampini/rampini-con1.html |work=Conversations with History |publisher= Institute of International Studies, [[UC Berkeley]] |date=25 September 2002 |access-date=3 January 2020}}</ref> He attended the [[European School, Brussels I]], where he earned a [[European Baccalaureate]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\" /> He then attended [[Bocconi University]] in Milan, where he spent four years studying [[political economy]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\" /> Subsequently, he attended the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where his contemporaries included, amongst others, [[Mario Draghi]]. He would also attend seminars of the French liberal sociologist [[Raymond Aron]] at the ''[[\u00c9cole pratique des hautes \u00e9tudes]]'' in Paris. He was a member of the [[Italian Communist Party]] from 1974 to 1984.\n\nRampini is married to Stefania, with whom he has two children, actor Jacopo Rampini and Costanza Rampini a university professor.  He has lived in the United States since 2000, and became a US citizen in 2014.<ref name=\"Federico Rampini\"/>\n\n==Career==\nRampini\u2019s activity as a journalist began in 1977 in \"Citt\u00e0 futura\", a weekly magazine of the [[Italian Communist Youth Federation]] (FGCI) whose secretary at the time was [[Massimo D\u2019Alema]]. From 1979 to 1982 he worked as the economic-union editor for the PCI weekly [[Rinascita]]. In 1982 Rampini moved to '' Mondo Economico '' (weekly of [[Il Sole 24 Ore]]) then to '' [[L'Espresso]] '' (1982-1986). Rampini worked for '' [[Il Sole 24 Ore]] '' as correspondent from [[France]] for five years (1986-1991) and later as deputy director (1991-1995). Since 1995 he has been working for ''[[La Repubblica]]'', first at the head of the Milanese editorial staff, then as foreign correspondent from [[Brussels]] (1997-2000), [[San Francisco]] (2000-2004), [[Beijing]] (2004-2009), and since 2009 from [[New York City|New York]]. Rampini often reports on top-level international summits such as the [[G8|G-8]],[[G-20]], and the [[World Economic Forum]] in [[Davos]]; he also reports from the [[White House]] as he holds press accreditation from the Presidency of the [[United States of America]].\n\nRampini, who is a prolific non-fiction writer and essayist, has written over 30 books, most of which are published by [[Mondadori]] and have been translated into several languages. In 2005, his book [[Il Secolo Cinese]] -\"The Chinese Century\", topped the Italian bestseller charts in non-fiction for several months and is now in its sixteenth edition. His 2006 book [[L'Impero di Cindia]] - \"The Chindia Empire: China, India and Their Surroundings\" ([[Mondadori]]), sold over 100,000 copies.\n\nRampini was named among the fifty most influential personalities in Europe in 2005 by the European Voice poll ''EV50''. He has been a visiting professor at the [[University of California Berkeley]] School of Journalism, [[Bocconi]] University in Milan, and at the [[Shanghai University]] of Economics and Finance.\n\nRampini was accused in early 2015, among others by translator Marion Sarah Tuggey, of having based his articles and essays on translations and reductions of articles and reports from newspapers such as the [[New York Times]] and the [[Financial Times]]. Among these, an interview with [[Vandana Shiva]], which would have been produced through partial translation and readjustment of a blog post on Shiva's website.<ref>[http://vandanashiva.com/?p=105 Vandana Shiva] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910051019/http://vandanashiva.com/?p=105 |date=10 settembre 2015 }}, 26 agosto 2014; [http://www.repubblica.it/ambiente/2014/10/03/news/intervista_vandana_shiva_ogm-97215746/ Repubblica], 3 ottobre 2014</ref><ref name=\"Libernazione\">[http://libernazione.it/shiva-e-rampini-cosa-aspettarsi-mai/ Luca Mazzone] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820170154/http://libernazione.it/shiva-e-rampini-cosa-aspettarsi-mai/ |date=20 agosto 2016 }}, 3 ottobre 2014</ref> \nTo illustrate such cases of plagiarism, Tuggey and others used the hashtag #rampinomics.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/grande-firma-repubblica-contagiata-virus-copia-e-incolla-1102996.html|title = La grande firma di \"Repubblica\" contagiata dal virus del copia e incolla|date = 4 January 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/personaggi/11755681/Federico-Rampini-sbugiardato-da-una-donna.html Libero], 12 febbraio 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.italiaoggi.it/giornali/dettaglio_giornali.asp?preview=false&accessMode=FA&id=1961481&codiciTestate=1 Italia Oggi], 12 febbraio 2015</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* [[Premio Acqui Storia]] , ''2005''\n* [[Premio Luigi Barzini]] , ''2005''\n* [[Premio Saint Vincent]], ''2006''\n* [[Premio Hemingway]] (2019)<ref name=\"hemingwayaward\" />\n\n==Books==\n{{div col}}\n* ''La comunicazione aziendale. All'interno dell'impresa, nel contesto sociale, nel quadro europeo'', Milano, ETAS libri, 1990, {{ISBN|88-453-0404-3}}\n* ''Il crack delle nostre pensioni'', Milano, Rizzoli, 1994, {{ISBN|88-17-84362-8}}.\n* ''Imprenditori italiani nel mondo. Ieri e oggi'', con Duccio Bigazzi (a cura di), Milano, Libri Scheiwiller, 1996, {{ISBN|88-7644-241-3}}.\n* ''Germanizzazione. Come cambier\u00e0 l'Italia'', Roma, Laterza, 1996, {{ISBN|88-420-4909-3}}.\n* ''Kosovo. Gli italiani e la guerra'', intervista a [[Massimo D'Alema]], Milano, Mondadori, 1999, {{ISBN|88-04-47302-9}}.\n* ''Per adesso. Intervista con [[Carlo De Benedetti]]'', Milano, Longanesi, 1999, {{ISBN|88-304-1473-5}}.\n* ''New economy. Una rivoluzione in corso'', Roma, Laterza, 2000, {{ISBN|88-420-6110-7}}.\n* ''Dall'euforia al crollo. La seconda vita della new economy'', Roma, Laterza, 2001, {{ISBN|88-420-6821-7}}.\n* ''Effetto euro'', Milano, Longanesi, 2002, {{ISBN|88-304-1934-6}}.\n* ''Le paure dell'America'', Collana I Robinson.Letture, Milano, Longanesi, 2003, {{ISBN|88-420-7167-6}}.\n* ''San Francisco-Milano'', Collana Contromano, Roma, Laterza, Laterza 2004, {{ISBN|88-420-7441-1}}.\n* ''Tutti gli uomini del presidente. George W. Bush e la nuova destra americana'', Collana Le sfere, Roma, Carocci, 2004, {{ISBN|88-430-3013-2}}.\n* ''[[Il secolo cinese]]. Storie di uomini, citt\u00e0 e denaro dalla fabbrica del mondo'', Milano, Mondadori, 2005, {{ISBN|88-04-54482-1}}.\n* ''L'impero di Cindia. Cina, India e dintorni: la superpotenza asiatica da tre miliardi e mezzo di persone'', Collana Strade blu, Milano, Mondadori, 2006, {{ISBN|88-04-55130-5}}.\n* ''L'ombra di Mao. Sulle tracce del grande timoniere per capire il presente di Cina, Tibet, Corea del Nord e il futuro del mondo'', Milano, Mondadori, 2006, {{ISBN|88-04-56048-7}}.\n* ''La speranza indiana. Storie di uomini, citt\u00e0 e denaro dalla pi\u00f9 grande democrazia del mondo'', Collana Strade blu, Milano, Mondadori 2007, {{ISBN|88-04-57298-1}}.\n* ''Centomila punture di spillo. Come l'Italia pu\u00f2 tornare a correre'', con [[Carlo De Benedetti]] e [[Francesco Daveri]], Collana Strade blu, Milano, Mondadori 2008, {{ISBN|88-04-58366-5}}.\n* ''Con gli occhi dell'Oriente'', Milano, A. Mondadori scuola, 2009.\n* ''Le dieci cose che non saranno pi\u00f9 le stesse. Tutto quello che la crisi sta cambiando'', Roma, Gruppo editoriale L'Espresso, 2009.\n* ''Slow Economy. Rinascere con saggezza. Tutto quello che noi occidentali possiamo imparare dall'Oriente'', Collana Strade blu, Milano, Mondadori 2009. {{ISBN|978-88-04-59368-3}}.\n* ''Occidente estremo. Il nostro futuro tra l'ascesa dell'impero cinese e il declino della potenza americana'', Collana Strade blu, Milano, Mondadori 2010. {{ISBN|978-88-04-60333-7}}<ref name=\"Federico Rampini racconta l'Occidente estremo\">[http://genova.mentelocale.it/31293-l-occidente-estremo-di-federico-rampini-tra-l-ascesa-dell-impero-cinese-e-il-declino-della-potenza-americana/ Federico Rampini racconta 'L'Occidente estremo'] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110925010818/http://genova.mentelocale.it/31293-l-occidente-estremo-di-federico-rampini-tra-l-ascesa-dell-impero-cinese-e-il-declino-della-potenza-americana/ |date=25 settembre 2011 }}, mentelocale.it.</ref>\n* {{cite book|title=San Francisco-Milano. Un italiano nell'altra America|edition=Collana I Robinson.Letture|location=Roma-Bari|publisher=Laterza|year=2011|isbn=978-88-420-9517-0}}\n* {{cite book|title=Alla mia sinistra. Lettera aperta a tutti quelli che vogliono sognare insieme a me|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2011|isbn=978-88-04-61372-5}}\n* {{cite book|title=\"Non ci possiamo pi\u00f9 permettere uno Stato sociale\". Falso!|edition=Collana Id\u00f2la|publisher=Laterza|location=Roma-Bari|year=2012|isbn=978-88-420-9502-6}}\n* {{cite book|title=Voi avete gli orologi, noi abbiamo il tempo. Manifesto generazionale per non rinunciare al futuro|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2012|isbn=978-88-04-62518-6}}\n* {{cite book|title=Banchieri. Storie dal nuovo banditismo globale|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2013|isbn=978-88-04-63350-1}}\n* {{cite book|author=[[Giorgio Napolitano]]|title=La via maestra. L'Europa e il ruolo dell'Italia nel mondo. Conversazione con Federico Rampini|edition=Collana Ingrandimenti|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2013|isbn=978-88-046-3247-4}}\n* {{cite book|title=Vi racconto il nostro futuro. Con DVD. Occidente estremo, lo spettacolo teatrale. Libro + DVD|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2014|isbn=978-88-046-3863-6}}\n* {{cite book|title=La trappola dell'austerity. Perch\u00e9 l'ideologia del rigore blocca la ripresa|publisher=Laterza|location=Roma-Bari|year=2014|isbn=978-88-581-1163-5}}\n* {{cite book|title=Rete padrona. Amazon. Apple, Google & co. Il volto oscuro della rivoluzione digitale|publisher=Feltrinelli|location=Milano|year=2014|isbn=978-88-07-07036-5}}\n* {{cite book|title=All you need is love. L'economia spiegata con le canzoni dei Beatles|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2014|isbn=978-88-04-64590-0}}\n* {{cite book|title=L'et\u00e0 del caos. Viaggio nel grande disordine mondiale|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2015|isbn=978-88-04-65807-8}}\n* {{cite book|title=Banche: possiamo ancora fidarci?|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2016|isbn=978-88-04-66140-5}}\n* {{cite book|title=Il tradimento. Globalizzazione e immigrazione, le menzogne delle \u00e9lite|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2016|isbn=978-88-04-67241-8}}\n* {{cite book|title=Le linee rosse. Uomini, Confini, Imperi: le carte geografiche che raccontano il mondo in cui viviamo|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2017|isbn=978-88-04-68358-2}}\n* {{cite book|title=Quando inizia la nostra storia. Le grandi svolte del passato che hanno disegnato il mondo in cui viviamo|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2018|isbn=978-88-04-70529-1}}\n* {{cite book|title=La notte della sinistra. Da dove ripartire|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2019|isbn=978-88-04-71340-1}}\n* {{cite book|title=L'oceano di mezzo. Un viaggio lungo 24.539 km|edition=Collana I Robinson|publisher=Laterza|location=Roma-Bari|year=2019|isbn=978-88-581-3687-4}}\n* {{cite book|title=La seconda guerra fredda. Lo scontro per il nuovo dominio globale|edition=Collana Strade blu|publisher=Mondadori|location=Milano|year=2019|isbn=978-88-047-1873-4}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rampini, Federico}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian journalists]]\n[[Category:Italian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Italian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian writers]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the European Schools]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian journalist and writer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Federico Rampini\n| image         = Federico Rampini - Festival Economia 2015.JPG\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1956|03|25}}\n| birth_place   = Genoa, Italy\n| nationality   = Italian, American\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Journalist, writer, lecturer\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Federico Rampini''' (born 25 March 1956) is an Italian [[journalist]], [[writer]], and [[lecturer]] who holds both Italian and American citizenship.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/trump-trashes-us-allies-china-seizes-future/|title=While Trump Trashes US Allies, China Seizes the Future|last=Rampini|first=Federico|date=12 June 2018|journal=[[The Nation]]|location=U.S.|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iicchicago.esteri.it/iic_chicago/it/gli_eventi/calendario/book-presentation-when-our-history.html|title=Book Presentation: \"When Our History Begins\" by Federico Rampini, Chief New York Correspondent for Italy's La Repubblica Newspaper|website=iicchicago.esteri.it|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Italy)]]|location=Italy|language=it-it|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>  He served as deputy editor of ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'', and has worked as chief  foreign correspondent for ''[[La Repubblica]]'' since 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ces.fas.harvard.edu/people/federico-rampini|title=Federico Rampini|last=University|first=Harvard|date=20 November 2019|website=Center for European Studies at Harvard University|publisher=[[Harvard University]]|location=Massachusetts, U.S.|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref> He has been residing in the United States since 2000.<ref name=\"Federico Rampini\">{{cite web|url=http://www.premiohemingway.it|title=Federico Rampini|accessdate=24 August 2019}}</ref> He is the 2019 receipient of the [[Premio Hemingway|Ernest Hemmingway Prize]].<ref name=\"hemingwayaward\">{{cite web |title=Federico Rampini Premio Hemingway 2019 per la sezione \"Testimone del nostro tempo\" {{!}} 35^ Edizione del Premio Hemingway 19 / 23 GIUGNO 2019 - LIGNANO |url=http://www.premiohemingway.it/all-event-list/federico-rampini-premio-hemingway-2019-per-la-sezione-testimone-del-nostro-tempo/ |website=www.premiohemingway.it |accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life, education and family==\nRampini was born in [[Genoa]], Italy on March 25, 1956, and was raised in [[Brussels]] due to his father's work at the [[European Commission]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\">{{cite interview |last=Rampini |first=Federico |interviewer=[[Harry Kreisler]] |title=Federico Rampini Interview {{!}} Background |type=Transcript of video |url=http://globetrotter.berkeley.edu/people2/Rampini/rampini-con1.html |work=Conversations with History |publisher= Institute of International Studies, [[UC Berkeley]] |date=25 September 2002 |access-date=3 January 2020}}</ref> He attended the [[European School, Brussels I]], where he earned a [[European Baccalaureate]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\" /> He then attended [[Bocconi University]] in Milan, where he spent four years studying [[political economy]].<ref name=\"KreislerInterviewBackground\" /> Subsequently, he attended the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where his contemporaries included, amongst others, [[Mario Draghi]]. He would also attend seminars of the French liberal sociologist [[Raymond Aron]] at the ''[[\u00c9cole pratique des hautes \u00e9tudes]]'' in Paris. He was a member of the [[Italian Communist Party]] from 1974 to 1984.\n\nRampini is married to Stefania, with whom he has two children, actor Jacopo Rampini and Costanza Rampini a university professor.  He has lived in the United States since 2000, and became a US citizen in 2014.<ref name=\"Federico Rampini\"/>\n\n==Career==\nRampini\u2019s activity as a journalist began in 1977 in \"Citt\u00e0 futura\", a weekly magazine of the [[Italian Communist Youth Federation]] (FGCI) whose secretary at the time was [[Massimo D\u2019Alema]]. From 1979 to 1982 he worked as the economic-union editor for the PCI weekly [[Rinascita]]. In 1982 Rampini moved to '' Mondo Economico '' (weekly of [[Il Sole 24 Ore]]) then to '' [[L'Espresso]] '' (1982-1986). Rampini worked for '' [[Il Sole 24 Ore]] '' as correspondent from [[France]] for five years (1986-1991) and later as deputy director (1991-1995). Since 1995 he has been working for ''[[La Repubblica]]'', first at the head of the Milanese editorial staff, then as foreign correspondent from [[Brussels]] (1997-2000), [[San Francisco]] (2000-2004), [[Beijing]] (2004-2009), and since 2009 from [[New York City|New York]]. Rampini often reports on top-level international summits such as the [[G8|G-8]],[[G-20]], and the [[World Economic Forum]] in [[Davos]]; he also reports from the [[White House]] as he holds press accreditation from the Presidency of the [[United States of America]].\n\nRampini, who is a prolific non-fiction writer and essayist, has written over 30 books, most of which are published by [[Mondadori]] and have been translated into several languages. In 2005, his book [[Il Secolo Cinese]] -\"The Chinese Century\", topped the Italian bestseller charts in non-fiction for several months and is now in its sixteenth edition. His 2006 book [[L'Impero di Cindia]] - \"The Chindia Empire: China, India and Their Surroundings\" ([[Mondadori]]), sold over 100,000 copies.\n\nRampini was named among the fifty most influential personalities in Europe in 2005 by the European Voice poll ''EV50''. He has been a visiting professor at the [[University of California Berkeley]] School of Journalism, [[Bocconi]] University in Milan, and at the [[Shanghai University]] of Economics and Finance.\n\nRampini was accused in early 2015, among others by translator Marion Sarah Tuggey, of having based his articles and essays on translations and reductions of articles and reports from newspapers such as the [[New York Times]] and the [[Financial Times]]. Among these, an interview with [[Vandana Shiva]], which would have been produced through partial translation and readjustment of a blog post on Shiva's website.<ref>[http://vandanashiva.com/?p=105 Vandana Shiva] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910051019/http://vandanashiva.com/?p=105 |date=10 settembre 2015 }}, 26 agosto 2014; [http://www.repubblica.it/ambiente/2014/10/03/news/intervista_vandana_shiva_ogm-97215746/ Repubblica], 3 ottobre 2014</ref><ref name=\"Libernazione\">[http://libernazione.it/shiva-e-rampini-cosa-aspettarsi-mai/ Luca Mazzone] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820170154/http://libernazione.it/shiva-e-rampini-cosa-aspettarsi-mai/ |date=20 agosto 2016 }}, 3 ottobre 2014</ref> \nTo illustrate such cases of plagiarism, Tuggey and others used the hashtag #rampinomics. <ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/grande-firma-repubblica-contagiata-virus-copia-e-incolla-1102996.html|title = La grande firma di \"Repubblica\" contagiata dal virus del copia e incolla|date = 4 January 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/personaggi/11755681/Federico-Rampini-sbugiardato-da-una-donna.html Libero], 12 febbraio 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.italiaoggi.it/giornali/dettaglio_giornali.asp?preview=false&accessMode=FA&id=1961481&codiciTestate=1 Italia Oggi], 12 febbraio 2015</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* [[Premio Acqui Storia]] , ''2005''\n* [[Premio Luigi Barzini]] , ''2005''\n* [[Premio Saint Vincent]], ''2006''\n* [[Premio Hemingway]] (2019)<ref name=\"hemingwayaward\" />\n\n==Books==\n{{div col}}\n* ''La comunicazione aziendale. All'interno dell'impresa, nel contesto sociale, nel quadro europeo'', Milano, ETAS libri, 1990, {{ISBN|88-453-0404-3}}\n* ''Il crack delle nostre pensioni'', Milano, Rizzoli, 1994, {{ISBN|88-17-84362-8}}.\n* ''Imprenditori italiani nel mondo. Ieri e oggi'', con Duccio Bigazzi (a cura di), Milano, Libri Scheiwiller, 1996, {{ISBN|88-7644-241-3}}.\n* ''Germanizzazione. Come cambier\u00e0 l'Italia'', Roma, Laterza, 1996, {{ISBN|88-420-4909-3}}.\n* ''Kosovo. Gli italiani e la guerra'', intervista a [[Massimo D'Alema]], Milano, Mondadori, 1999, {{ISBN|88-04-47302-9}}.\n* ''Per adesso. Intervista con [[Carlo De Benedetti]]'', Milano, Longanesi, 1999, {{ISBN|88-304-1473-5}}.\n* ''New economy. Una rivoluzione in corso'', Roma, Laterza, 2000, {{ISBN|88-420-6110-7}}.\n* ''Dall'euforia al crollo. La seconda vita della new economy'', Roma, Laterza, 2001, {{ISBN|88-420-6821-7}}.\n* ''Effetto euro'', Milano, Longanesi, 2002, {{ISBN|88-304-1934-6}}.\n* ''Le paure dell'America'', Collana I Robinson.Letture, Milano, Longanesi, 2003, {{ISBN|88-420-7167-6}}.\n* ''San Francisco-Milano'', Collana Contromano, Roma, Laterza, Laterza 2004,