ty-first century|last=1969-|first=Aldama, Frederick Luis|date=2013|publisher=University of Michigan Press|isbn=9780472029129|location=Ann Arbor|oclc=844924402}}</ref> (University of Michigan Press, 2013)\n* ''Latinos and Narrative Media: Participation and Portrayal''<ref>{{Cite book|title=Latinos and narrative media : participation and portrayal|others=Aldama, Frederick Luis, 1969-|isbn=9781137366450|edition= First|location=New York|oclc=845085678|date = 2013-11-07}}</ref> (Palgrave, 2013)\n* ''\u00a1Muy Pop! Conversations on Latino Popular Culture.'' Co-authored with Ilan Stavans<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u00a1Muy Pop! : conversations on Latino popular culture|last=Ilan.|first=Stavans|others=Aldama, Frederick Luis, 1969-|isbn=9780472029440|location=Ann Arbor, Michigan|oclc=874149423}}</ref> (University of Michigan, 2013)\n* ''Latinos in the End Zone: Conversations on the Brown Color Line in the NFL.'' Co-authored with Christopher Gonz\u00e1lez<ref>{{Cite book|title=Latinos in the end zone : conversations on the brown color line in the NFL|last=1969-|first=Aldama, Frederick Luis|others=Gonz\u00e1lez, Christopher|isbn=978-1137403087|edition= First|location=New York, NY|oclc=860395198|date = 2013-11-15}}</ref> (Palgrave, 2013)\n* ''Conversations on Cognitive Cultural Studies: Literature, Language, Aesthetics.'' Co-authored with Patrick Colm Hogan<ref>{{Cite book|title=Conversations on cognitive cultural studies : literature, language, and aesthetics|last=1969-|first=Aldama, Frederick Luis|others=Hogan, Patrick Colm|isbn=9780814212431|location=Columbus|oclc=861955952|year = 2014}}</ref> (Ohio State U Press, 2014)\n* ''The Cinema of Robert Rodriguez''<ref>{{Cite book|title=The cinema of Robert Rodriguez|last=1969-|first=Aldama, Frederick Luis|isbn=9780292761216|edition= First|location=Austin|oclc=878667406|date = 2014-10-15}}</ref>''.'' (University of Texas Press, 2014)\n* ''Critical Approaches to the Films of Robert Rodriguez.''<ref>{{Cite book|title=Critical approaches t